From: stopless-java-gc <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH 0031/N] posix/bsd: non-Apple BSD aarch64 fixups (W^X, MAP_NORESERVE, link_map)

Further FreeBSD/CheriBSD shared-source surprises that surfaced after
patch 0030. None are CHERI-specific; they reflect the fact that
OpenJDK 17u has only ever been built on Darwin in the BSD family.

src/hotspot/os/bsd/os_bsd.cpp
  - get_summary_cpu_info: my patch 0030 moved `size_t size` into the
    `#ifdef __APPLE__` branch, leaving it undeclared on the FreeBSD
    side. Declare `size_t size;` in the non-Apple branch as well.
  - get_loaded_modules_info: `struct link_map` requires `<link.h>`
    (which HotSpot does not include here) and the field layout
    differs from Solaris. Easier to gate the body off on FreeBSD
    entirely — the function returns 1 (callers treat as "no data"),
    matching the existing fallthrough behavior on other BSD.
  - MAP_NORESERVE is a Linux-ism the upstream code uses
    unconditionally on the BSD side. FreeBSD doesn't define it (its
    semantics are the default). Add `#define MAP_NORESERVE 0` as a
    pure no-op for the `|` chain.

src/hotspot/os/posix/os_posix.cpp
  - Same MAP_NORESERVE define for the posix-side mmap call sites.
  - Stack expansion code calls `os::Linux::manually_expand_stack`
    even from the shared posix file. Wrap in `#ifdef LINUX`; on
    BSD the stack auto-grows and the recursive-segv fatal branch
    is correct.

src/hotspot/os_cpu/bsd_aarch64/os_bsd_aarch64.cpp
  - `ThreadWXEnable` and `os::current_thread_enable_wx`
    (`pthread_jit_write_protect_np`) are Apple aarch64 JIT W^X
    helpers. Wrap their definitions and the signal-handler call
    site in `#ifdef __APPLE__`. Phase 1 (interpreter-only) doesn't
    need JIT W^X on CheriBSD; the cap_runtime barrier patches in
    Phase 2 will revisit if needed.

Refs: docs/05_zgc_cheri_collision_report.md §6 (patch 0031)

--- a/src/hotspot/os/bsd/os_bsd.cpp
+++ b/src/hotspot/os/bsd/os_bsd.cpp
@@ -69,6 +69,13 @@
 #include "utilities/growableArray.hpp"
 #include "utilities/vmError.hpp"

+#ifndef MAP_NORESERVE
+// FreeBSD/CheriBSD does not have MAP_NORESERVE; the equivalent semantics
+// (do not reserve swap up-front) are the FreeBSD default. Define as 0 so
+// it ORs into mmap flags as a no-op.
+#define MAP_NORESERVE 0
+#endif
+
 // put OS-includes here
 # include <dlfcn.h>
 # include <errno.h>
@@ -1271,7 +1278,7 @@
 }

 int os::get_loaded_modules_info(os::LoadedModulesCallbackFunc callback, void *param) {
-#ifdef RTLD_DI_LINKMAP
+#if defined(RTLD_DI_LINKMAP) && !defined(__FreeBSD__)
   Dl_info dli;
   void *handle;
   struct link_map *map;
@@ -1420,6 +1427,7 @@
 #else
   // FreeBSD/CheriBSD: HW_CPU_FREQ is macOS-specific; stub for Phase 1.
   unsigned int mhz = 0;
+  size_t size;
 #endif

   char model[100];
